  <h2>Student Quick-Start Guide</h2>
  <p>Getting started with Karooly is easy:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Create an account and <%= link_to 'sign in', new_user_session_path %> </li>
    <li>Go to the lesson you were assigned, and enroll. Make sure your username appears on the enrolled list (at the bottom of the page)</li>
    <li>Browse through the lesson's content (go to each individual word, and click its audio)</li>
    <li>Complete the "Exposition" activity as many times as you feel necessary to get a sense of the word and its spelling</li>
    <li>Complete the "Unscramble" and "Dictation" activities</li>
    <li>Do the "Spelling" activity last, as a way to quiz yourself</li>
    <li>Once you complete all activities, you will see a <i class="fa fa-check-circle" style="color:green;" aria-hidden="true"></i> next to your username at the bottom of the list</li>
  </ol>
  <p>Also keep in mind:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>You can keep track of the lessons you've enrolled through your dashboard (click on your username on the top navigation bar when you're signed in)</li>
    <li>You can print the lesson's vocabulary (images and terms) if you like having a physical copy for reference. Just click on the icon on the main lesson page</li>
    <li>You will <strong>learn faster and more securely</strong> if you avoid translating back-and-forth with English. Should you need to consult the references, try to get a sense for the vocabulary first with the images alone</li>
  </ul>

