  <a name="app"></a>
  <h2>Can I learn a language just by using Karooly?</h2>
  <p>Multiple studies posit that language is best learned through communication (expressing oneself orally, reading, writing, etc.). To reach second-language proficiency you need to interact with people, just like you did when learning your native tongue as a young child. Karooly is a tool to promote vocabulary acquisition and proper spelling. Some added benefits are that students don't need to carry around paper vocabulary handouts, and that teachers don't need to go over terms in a menial manner.</p><br>

